      <div class="text
  
  
  
  js-text
  ">
      <h2 class="
      text__header
      
      
            ">
              <a  class="
        text__header-link
        
        text__header-link--dark"
        href="https://sji.uic.edu/portal-project/participants?go=front">Over 100 Scholars and Activists</a>
          </h2>
  
      <div class="text__text" ><p>We have invited national and international activists, community-based scholars, and researchers to join us. They represent every region of the country and have a depth of experience. Together they will engage in organized conversation, collaboration, learning and knowledge production. Their expertise includes in immigrant rights, economic and electoral justice, anti-violence and gender justice, abolition, climate justice, anti-racism, and a range of other issues.</p>
<p>The 2020–2021 cohort of Marielle Franco and Margaret Burroughs Fellows represent a powerful group of critical scholars and social movement leaders. The Fellows will collaborate in activist-led working groups to produce written documents and educational resources related to key social justice themes. We are excited to announce that the inaugural cohort of Franco Fellows include:</p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400">Angela Y. Davis</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400">Keeanga-Yamahtta Taylor</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400">Naomi Klein</li>
<li style="font-weight: 400">Robin D.G. Kelley</li>
</ul>
</div>
